review_blob: 750ml - Bready yeast aroma with white pepper and tropical fruit.  Flavor of banana and mango, spicy yeast and a touch of citrus hops.  Palate is tangy and spicy.  Nice American tripel.

750ml - Crisp hoppy aroma, pine and citrus.  Followed by sweet doughy yeast.  Flavor is the opposite by starting sweet and doughy and finishing with fruity hops.  Palate is tart and sticky.  Very nice twist on tradition.

750ml - Funky aroma pulls me in from across the table.  Chewy bread yeast, spicy, funky with some citrus hops.  Flavor is full of sour citrus fruit, chewy hops and spicy yeast.  Palate is crisp, tart and tangy.  A wonderful saison.

750ml - Sweet malty aroma with wheat, subtle citrus hops and a touch of oak.  Flavor is full of wheat and malt with a sweet wine like finish.  Also some hops and oak.  Palate is dry and sticky.  Interesting and pretty good.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Harvest Dance Wheat Wine

review_blob: 500ml - Aroma of fruity hops, chewy caramel malt with some more hops both spicy citrus and floral.  Flavor is perfectly balanced mix of multiple hops flavors and caramel malt.  Palate is sweet and tart.  A great IPA.

22oz - Aroma of soft chewy yeast which leads into orange peel, oak and white wine.  Flavor is tasty but mellow.  Sour yeast, orange and a touch of oak and wine.  Palate is soft and creamy.  Subtle yet full flavored.

12oz - Pungent aroma of soy, molasses, burnt dark malts, chocolate and vanilla.  Flavor is very intense.  Tons of molasses, chocolate and vanilla.  Chewy dark malts leave a dusty aftertaste.  Palate is very bitter, then sweet and sticky.  Interested to see how time treats this one.  It isnt something I would want to drink more than one of at a time right now.

Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Last beer of the night.  Aroma is loaded with dark malts, chocolate and vanilla.  Flavor is sweet chocolate, burnt dark malts, vanilla and coffee.  Palate is sweet and dry.  A great beer that deserves a fair shake with a fresher palate.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is deep dark malts, vanilla and dark chocolate.  The flavor is crazy full of of chocolate malts and vanilla.  Palate is smooth and creamy.  Wow a fantastically tasty beer.  I have to admit, by this point in the tasting, I was feeling it.  But this beer still blew me away.  I want more!
Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is smokey dark malts and sweet black licorice.  Flavor matches with the 13.6% well hidden under a smooth clean palate.  Not bad but isnt grabbing me.

Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is loaded with dark malts and fruits followed by dusty dry coffee.  Flavor is strong match to aroma but finishes thin.  Palate is chewy.  A nice twist to traditional BA imperial stouts.

Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is oak, sweet caramel malt, wheat and maple.  Flavor is maltier and heavy with vanilla, maple, caramel and oak.  Alcohol is well hidden or I was starting to feel the other samples.  Palate is sweet and tart.  A nice brew I would like to have again.

Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is funky, oak, sour cherry, sweet caramel malts and some dark fruit.  Flavor is loaded with the same stuff and more.  A complex beer that hides the alcohol well.  Palate is sticky and sour.  A damn nice brew.

Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is initially a tad oxidized but is quickly overtaken by caramel and prune.  Flavor is full of caramel, prune and raisin.  Palate is very smooth.  Ive had this bottle for at least 3 years and no telling how old it was.  Thinking I should have popped it earlier, but still a good brew.

Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is straw, pale malts, bready yeast, honey, sweet fruit with a touch of hops.  Flavor has a lot more hops but otherwise matches aroma.  Palate is sticky and tart.  Alcohol is well hidden as I would not have guessed 10% until I read it.  A nice and drinkable American triple

Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is loaded with berries, fruit roll-up and Wonka Runts fruit candy.  Flavor is sweet berry candy with a real sour fruit back.  Palate is sticky and tart.  The berry flavor is so strong and overwhelming, I just couldnt get into it.

Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is pungent roasted dark malts, bourbon, oak and vanilla.  Flavor matches but is not overwhelming full of bourbon at all.  The palate is very creamy, lush and smooth.  A very nice bourbon barrel beer.
beer_name: Cigar City Bolita Double Nut Brown Ale - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is strong apple brandy, alcohol, wood and caramel.  Flavor is sappy wood, caramel, vinegar and cherry.  Palate is sticky and dry.  Another special treat, thanks Sprinkle!

Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - 6-9-2003 - Aroma is stanky...just the way I like it.  Dry dusty barnyard, horse blanket and a touch of fruit lingering somewhere behind it all.  The flavor matches but is a little more subtle, softened by oak and vanilla.  Palate is mouth watering tart.  Nice and funky.  Thanks Sprinkle!
beer_name: 3 Fonteinen J & J Oude Geuze Blauw

review_blob: Sampled at Feb 2010 Indy tasting - Aroma is pungent sour cherry, red wine vinegar and oak.  Flavor is more subtle but still very nice.  Lots of wet oak and sour cherry.  Palate is sticky and sour.  Very nice brew Id love to get again.

Pint at Brugge in Indy - Aroma of oak, rye, cherry and spicy citrus piney hops. Flavor matches with some smokey leather thrown in.  Palate is dry and sticky.  Very different with an intense flavor you need to be in the mood for.
beer_name: Schlafly / New Albanian / OFallon C1 Collaboration Ale

review_blob: Tulip at Brugge - Pungent aroma of spicy yeast and sticky malts.  Even a little floral.  Flavor is strong bubblegum yeast and chewy caramel malt.  Palate is sweet and sticky.  A little too sweet for my taste, but still good.
beer_name: Brugge Brasserie Son of Thunder Monkey

review_blob: Pint - Aroma is subtle Noble hops, straw and pale malts.  Flavor matches with a touch more hops.  Palate is crisp and clean.  Overall, not a bad beer, just not very exciting or tasty.  Id drink it again if there was nothing else.

12oz - 2009 - Aroma is deep dark roasted malts and chocolate.  Flavor is bold yet very drinkable.  Lots of dark roasted malts, sweet chocolate and just a touch of hop bitterness.  Alcohol is well hidden.  Palate is creamy and dry.  A real nice brew.
beer_name: Left Hand Fade To Black Vol. 1: Foreign Stout

review_blob: 22oz and tap - Aroma of chewy hops and caramel malt.  Flavor of sour citrus hops and caramel malts.  Palate is tart and creamy.  Very drinkable IPA.

750ml - 2009 - A very boozy aroma.  Full of bourbon, vanilla and oak.  Flavor is also bourbon forward but has enough other stuff going on to balance it out.  Vanilla, oak, chocolate malt, alcohol and a touch of soy.  Palate is dry.  Big, complex and tasty.  A little too much bourbon for me but still a nice brew.
beer_name: Big Sky Ivan the Terrible Imperial Stout - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: 22oz - Crisp citrus hop aroma and caramel malt.  Flavor is chewy citrus hops with a nice balanced malt finish.  Palate is tart and creamy.  A good ipa.
12oz - Aroma of toasted malts and leather.  Flavor of caramel, toffee and toasted malts.  Palate is sticky.  Not a bad dark lager.
12oz - Aroma of rye, pale malts and some resin hops.  Flavor matches with a stronger hop finish.  Palate is tart and chewy.  Not bad.
12oz - Aroma of pale malts and citrus hops.  Flavor is wet sour malts, straw and sticky hops, but not the typical C-hops I would expect.  Palate is tart.  Its a pale ale...

12oz - Aroma of maple syrup and dark roasted malts.  Flavor is too strong on the maple almost artificial.  There is a decent dark malt finish.  Palate  is sticky.  Drinkable, but too more than one at a time.

12oz - Aroma of dark burnt skunk malts.  Flavor is mild dark malts but is a little funky.  I cant help thinking BMC lager which is not a good thing.  Palate is thin.  Ive had worse but not not looking for any more.
12oz - Aroma of wet malts, candi sugar and a touch of yeast.  Bland flavor that matches aroma.  Palate is sticky and tart.  Not so good, but drinkable.
22oz - Aroma has tons of chocolate malt, coffee and alcohol.  Flavor is sweet chocolate, tootsie roll and chewy dark malts.  Palate is sticky.  A very nice chocolate coffee stout.
22oz - Aroma of roasted malts,  lacto, chocolate and a touch of hops.  Flavor matches.  Palate is sweet and clean.  Tasty and drinkable.

500ml - Initial aroma is strong spices followed by roasted dark malts with a touch of hops.  Flavor is doughy chocolate cookies with holiday spices on top.  The JP yeast shows in the finish.  Palate is soft, creamy and spicy.  A very tasty and well balanced holiday brew.
beer_name: Ngne  / Jolly Pumpkin / Stone Special Holiday Ale

review_blob: 22oz - Aroma of sweet caramel malts and juicy citrus and pine hops.  Flavor is big tropical fruit, sour hops with a sweet finish.  Nice balance and the alcohol is well hidden.  Palate is sticky and sweet.  A nice brew.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Extra! Ale

review_blob: 750ml - Aroma of toasted malts, rye, chewy caramel malts and pine hops.  Flavor is crisp toasty malts and rye.  There is a wet sour mash of caramel malts too.  Palate is sticky and tart.  Different and a good winter brew.
12oz - Aroma of black licorice, peppermint, cinnamon and clove.  Flavor matches with some added chocolate.  Palate is spicy and tart.  A good holiday brew that might be too strong for some.

22oz - Aroma is full of caramel and resinous pine hops and a touch of oak.  Flavor starts with doughy caramel malts followed by tangy hops.  Palate starts creamy and finishes bitter.  A very tasty DIPA.
beer_name: Two Brothers Heavier Handed India Pale Ale

review_blob: 750ml - 2009 - 1300th rating - Pungent aroma of wet oak, horse blanket and strawberry.  Flavor is stronger strawberry with a big oak finish.  Still has the funky barnyard going on too.  Palate is tart and funky sour.  A very nice lambic.

750ml - 2009 - Aroma is strong.  Musty horse blanket, sharp yeast, oak and tart blackberry.  Flavor matches but isnt as musty and the berry really shines.  Palate is tart up front but finishes soft.  Very tasty.
750ml - Aroma is nutty, malty, chocolate, caramel and yeast.  Flavor matches with a strong chocolate finish.  Palate is sticky and tart.  Very nice Christmas brew.

500cl - Brewed 20 01 09 - Pungent aroma of alcohol, dark chocolate, burnt malts, chewy brownies and some dark fruits.  Flavor is intense but not in an astringent sort of way.  Dusty malts, dark chocolate, cocoa powder and dark fruit.  Palate is creamy and lush.  The 11% is hidden well.  A very nice winter warmer.
22oz - Pungent aroma of pine hops, dark roasted malts and chocolate.  Flavor matches with a big dark malt start and hoppy finish.  Palate is smooth and tart.  Very nice.

On tap at Noblesville brewery - Aroma is pungent with lots of brett and oak.  Flavor brings forward some toasted malts but quickly falls back to doughy yeast, oak and brett giving it a nice funky sour finish.  Palate is tart and creamy.  A fantastic sour that would draw some attention if it got out of the brewery.
beer_name: Barley Island Dirty "Old" Helen Sour Ale

review_blob: 22oz - Aroma of smoked malts, chocolate, caramel and crispy bacon.  Flavor is strong smoke, burnt chocolate malt, caramel, rye and meat cooked over a charcoal grill.  Palate is ashy and sticky.  If you like meaty smoked beers, give this one a try.
Tap - Sweet red licorice aroma with a pine hop back.    Flavor is very sweet caramel malt with a bitter hop finish.  Palate is syrupy and sticky.  Not offensive but too sweet for me.

Cask at the Noblesville brewery - Aroma of oak, vanilla, summit hops and caramel malt.  Bourbon forward flavor.  Dry and woody with vanilla, caramel and chewy hops.  Palate is smooth, creamy and balanced.  If you like bourbon and hops mixed, this beer is for you.
750ml - Aroma of doughy spicy yeast, straw, pale malts with subtle hops.  Flavor matched with a sweet finish.  Alcohol is well hidden,  Palate is sticky.  A flawless example of the style.
